Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil and sprinkle over
the @white cumin seeds{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss
to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{225%grams}, then cut it into 2cm chunks.

Place them into a small #bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Cut the @medium tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Zest and quarter the @lime{1}.

Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the
stalks).

In a large bowl, stir together the tomato, lime zest, half the lime juice, a
drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Remove the halloumi cubes from the cold water, pop them onto a plate lined
with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Wipe out the (now empty) small bowl and add the chopped mint and
@Greek style natural yoghurt{75%grams}. Mix together and season with salt and
pepper. Set your mint raita aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the halloumi and fry, turning frequently, until golden,
~{6-7%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and stir in the @mango chutney{40%grams} until the halloumi
is evenly glazed.

Once the potatoes are ready, mix them into the tomato bowl.

Share the potatoes and tomatoes between your serving bowls.

Drizzle over the mint raita, then top with the glazed halloumi.

Sprinkle over the @crispy onions{1%sachet} to finish.

Enjoy!